INDIA, TURKEY & GULF STATES — CHECK DAILY
These are active players in the Iran war and critical nodes in global trade/energy flows.

India:
India is the world's third-largest oil importer and largest buyer of Iranian crude (via intermediaries and dark fleet). Hormuz closure directly threatens India's energy security. India is also the world's largest generic pharmaceutical manufacturer — API supply chains transit the Red Sea.

Sources: Times of India, The Hindu, WION, Mint, Reuters India

Search: India oil imports Iran, India crude supply Hormuz, India API pharmaceutical supply, India food prices, India-Iran relations, Chabahar port, India BRICS mediation

Track: fuel price controls, strategic petroleum reserve drawdowns, diplomatic positioning, naval deployments

Turkey:
Controls the Bosphorus, NATO member, mediating between sides, hosts critical pipeline infrastructure (BTC, TANAP).

Sources: Daily Sabah, Hurriyet Daily News, Reuters Turkey

Search: Turkey mediation Iran, Turkey Bosphorus transit, Turkey energy pipeline, Erdogan Iran war

Track: diplomatic moves, refugee flows, energy transit, NATO positioning

Gulf States (UAE, Bahrain, Qatar, Kuwait, Oman):
Directly in the conflict zone. UAE/Bahrain taking strikes. Qatar is the world's largest LNG exporter (transit via Hormuz). Oman is a mediation channel to Iran.

