SECTION THRESHOLDS
NO threshold (always include if present):

Earnings: ANY watchlist company that filed gets full analysis.

LOWER threshold:

Climate & Ocean Systems: any anomalous measurement, record reading, new peer-reviewed circulation/ice research, or tipping-point indicator. Include climate-reinsurance cross-reference when material.

Commodities & Supply Chain: any confirmed disruption or price anomaly linked to Hormuz/Red Sea/war effects. ANY identified nonlinear ripple chain regardless of scale. Fertilizer, food, shipping rates, critical minerals, pharma APIs.

Insurance & Reinsurance: any change in war risk premiums, exclusion zones, P&I guidance, or cat bond pricing. Climate-reinsurance linkage.

Cyber & Threat Intel: critical infrastructure attacks, nation-state APT campaigns with attribution, mass-exploited zero-days, major supply chain compromises, new OFAC/EU sanctions designations affecting watchlist sectors. NOT routine CVEs or minor incidents.

Energy & Infrastructure: ANY confirmed fire, explosion, unscheduled outage, cable cut, or suspicious incident at energy infrastructure, subsea/terrestrial cables, or major data centers in US, Russia, or Europe. G3+ solar storms, X-class flares. Pattern recognition across incidents.

Ireland: government policy, Dail, courts, infrastructure, Irish tech, agriculture, Munster regional, r/ireland trending. Include Ireland-specific refugee/asylum and economic exposure items.

EU: major regulation, ECB, EP votes, EU-UK, CJEU, climate/energy.

Iran & Hormuz: military, shipping, sanctions, nuclear, Strait incidents. OSINT supplements: AIS anomalies in Strait, dark fleet movements, unusual military flights.

India, Turkey & Gulf States: any military, diplomatic, energy, or trade development involving these actors in the Iran conflict. Standard threshold for unrelated domestic politics.

Refugee & Humanitarian Flows: war-related displacement, Mediterranean crossings linked to conflict, Ireland asylum capacity. Standard threshold for routine migration.

Ukraine: 50+ missile salvos, territorial changes, major infrastructure, diplomatic shifts. OSINT supplements: ISW assessments, DeepState territorial changes, satellite damage verification.

